outstrip.translation[0].definitions[0].d: to do something better than someone else or be more successful
outstrip.translation[0].definitions[0].e: We outstripped all our competitors in sales last year.
outstrip.translation[0].definitions[1].d: to be greater in quantity than something else
outstrip.translation[0].definitions[1].e: Demand for new aircraft production is outstripping supply.
outstrip.translation[0].definitions[2].d: to run or move faster than someone or something else
outstrip.translation[0].definitions[2].e: Speeding at 90 mph, Denny outstripped police cars for an hour.
